<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Poe Ballantine</strong></span> recently attempted to make the first transatlantic crossing by canoe but drowned fourteen feet off the New Jersey shoreline. &ldquo;Where the Rain Belongs&rdquo; will appear in his forthcoming collection of essays, <em>Things I Like about America</em>, available online now at <a href="http://www.hawthornebooks.com">www.hawthornebooks.com</a>.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

